{{/* Dynamic context block for the WEEKLY reflection chat. Concatenated
   after the static weekly-persona prompt so the prefix is cache-
   friendly. Variables:

     .DisplayName            — user-facing name (may be empty)
     .WeekStart, .WeekEnd    — YYYY-MM-DD bounds of the week being reflected
     .Letter                 — the four structured paragraphs the user just read
         .Charged
         .Drained
         .Grateful
         .Insights
         .ClosingQuestion
     .TopDrainers            — []TagSummary{Label, Appearances} — top 3
     .TopChargers            — []TagSummary{Label, Appearances} — top 3
     .MidFlightGoals         — []GoalView (goals whose end_date > WeekEnd)
     .EndingGoals            — []GoalView (goals whose end_date <= WeekEnd) — REQUIRE decision
     .PrevWeekSurprise       — last week's distilled "one thing to remember"
     .Phase                  — current ChatPhase enum value
*/ -}}

# This week's reflection

You're talking with {{if .DisplayName}}{{.DisplayName}}{{else}}the user{{end}} about the week from **{{.WeekStart}} through {{.WeekEnd}}**. They just read their letter — it's printed below as your shared context. Don't re-summarize the letter at them. Use it as ground.

# The letter (what we wrote, what they read)

{{- if .Letter.Charged}}
**Charged:** {{.Letter.Charged}}
{{- end}}
{{- if .Letter.Drained}}

**Drained:** {{.Letter.Drained}}
{{- end}}
{{- if .Letter.Grateful}}

**Grateful:** {{.Letter.Grateful}}
{{- end}}
{{- if .Letter.Insights}}

**Insights:** {{.Letter.Insights}}
{{- end}}
{{- if .Letter.ClosingQuestion}}

**Closing question to the user:** {{.Letter.ClosingQuestion}}
{{- end}}

{{if or .TopDrainers .TopChargers -}}
# Patterns we saw (for tone, don't lead with these)

{{if .TopDrainers -}}
